- 375degF for 20-30m

=== cinnamon rolls

Dough:

- 1/2c milk (microwaved like 20s until it feels pleasantly warm to the touch but not too hot, probably 100-110degF)
- 1t   yeast
- 4T   butter
- 2T   sugar
- 1    egg
- 1/2t salt
- 2c   bread flour

Knead for 5m until smooth and stretchy, could use kitchenaid but I did it by hand.
I let rise for a couple hours room temperature, then overnight in the fridge, then
a couple hours to get back to room temperature.

Filling:
- 4T butter
- 1T cinnamon
- 1/4c  packed brown sugar

Mix until smooth. Roll out dough into a rectangle, spread filling,
roll up, cut into rolls. Put into parchment-lined (orig recipe says
"greased" but I just used parchment paper) pan, pour 1/2c heavy cream
over all of them.

I let sit for another 30-60m in a comfortably warm oven to proof some
more.

Bake at 375degF for 25-30m.

Frosting:
- 2T butter
- 2oz cream cheese
- dash salt
- 1/2c powdered sugar

=== cream biscuits

- 4/3c flour
- 1t salt
- 2t baking powder

Mix dry ingredients together

Add 2/3c cream, or a bit more, until dough comes together. Fold dough
onto itself a few times to make layers.

Flatten dough and cut into thin strips with bench scraper and lay
strips on their side.

425degF for 12m, then flip and 4m more.

=== sour cream biscuits (untested) [skip]

- 1c flour
- 1 stick butter softened
- 1/2c sour cream
- 1.5t baking powder
- dash salt

400degF for 20m

=== cheesecake

- 1lb cream cheese, room temperature
- 0.75c cups sugar
- 3 large eggs
- 1 cups heavy cream
- 1/2t kosher salt
- 1/2t vanilla extract
- 3T all-purpose flour

Line pan w parchment, make sure it's kind of high above the edge as the cake will rise.
Beat cream cheese and sugar. Continue beating, and add eggs, cream, salt, vanilla, flour.
Bake 400degF 60-65m.

