=== bread rolls [skip]

- 5c flour ≈ 600g
- 2c warm milk ≈ 450g
- 2t yeast
- 2t salt
- 2T butter

Reserve (subtract from the above)
- 45g flour for tangzhong (~1/3c)
- 225g milk               (1c)
for tangzhong

(by mass) ratio 1:5 flour to milk in making tangzhong
(by mass) 5-10% of the flour should be tangzhong

---

Half recipe
2.5c flour ≈ 300g
1c warm milk ≈ 225g
1t yeast
1t salt
1T butter

Reserve (subtract from the above)
22g of flour for tangzhong (~3T)
113g of milk               (1/2c)
for tangzhong

375degF 25m

Result: cakey texture. Maybe was underworked. Was underbaked.

